'''Boľkovce''' (before 1948 also ''Bolyk''; {{lang-hu| (Ipoly) bolyk }})   is a village and municipality in the [[Lučenec District]] in the [[Banská Bystrica Region]] of [[Slovakia]].

==History==
In [[history|historical records]], the [[village]] was first mentioned in 1320 and 1435 as ''Bolk'' (1467 ''Bwlyk'', 1481 ''Bolyk''). In 1481, it belonged to [[Divín]] Castle lords and later on to the Somoskő lords. In the mid-16th century it was occupied and destroyed by the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman Turks]], from 1938 to 1945 by [[Hungary]].
